<codeline><highlight class="normal">#<sp/>How<sp/>to<sp/>install<sp/>Blendercam<sp/>?</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">##<sp/>Use<sp/>Blendercam<sp/>from<sp/>github<sp/></highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">Using<sp/>Blendercam<sp/>from<sp/>github<sp/>is<sp/>a<sp/>great<sp/>way<sp/>to<sp/>try<sp/>out<sp/>the<sp/>newest<sp/>features<sp/>and<sp/>fixes.<sp/><sp/>The<sp/>latest<sp/>build<sp/>(dailybuild)<sp/>of<sp/>Blender<sp/>can<sp/>be<sp/>used<sp/>with<sp/>the<sp/>latest<sp/>Master<sp/>branch<sp/>of<sp/>Blendercam<sp/>and<sp/>then<sp/>you<sp/>can<sp/>live<sp/>on<sp/>the<sp/>bleeding<sp/>edge.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">The<sp/>easiest<sp/>way<sp/>to<sp/>&quot;install&quot;<sp/>is<sp/>not<sp/>to<sp/>install<sp/>but<sp/>instead<sp/>just<sp/>tell<sp/>Blender<sp/>where<sp/>to<sp/>find<sp/>the<sp/>add-on.<sp/><sp/>This<sp/>way<sp/>you<sp/>don&apos;t<sp/>have<sp/>to<sp/>worry<sp/>about<sp/>copying/moving<sp/>files<sp/>around.<sp/><sp/>You<sp/>can<sp/>keep<sp/>Blendercam<sp/>source<sp/>files<sp/>separate<sp/>from<sp/>Blender<sp/>if<sp/>using<sp/>source<sp/>control<sp/>(ie<sp/>git<sp/>for<sp/>development)<sp/>and<sp/>still<sp/>easily<sp/>test<sp/>your<sp/>changes<sp/>in<sp/>Blender.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
